          <source>Setting a Cursor&amp;#39;s Hot Spot (Image Editor for Icons)</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="103" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The hot spot of a <bpt id="p1">[</bpt>cursor<ept id="p1">](../mfc/icons-and-cursors-image-resources-for-display-devices-image-editor-for-icons.md)</ept> is the point to which Windows refers in tracking the cursor's position.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>By default, the hot spot is set to the upper-left corner of the cursor (coordinates 0,0).</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="105" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The Hotspot property in the <bpt id="p1">[</bpt>Properties window<ept id="p1">](/visualstudio/ide/reference/properties-window)</ept> shows the hot spot coordinates.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="106" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>To set a cursor's hot spot</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="107" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>On the <bpt id="p1">[</bpt>Image Editor toolbar<ept id="p1">](../mfc/toolbar-image-editor-for-icons.md)</ept>, click the <bpt id="p2">**</bpt>Set Hotspot<ept id="p2">**</ept> tool.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="108" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click the pixel you want to designate as the cursor's hot spot.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="109" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>Hotspot<ept id="p1">**</ept> property in the <bpt id="p2">**</bpt>Properties<ept id="p2">**</ept> window displays the new coordinates.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="110" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Tool tips appear when you hover your cursor over a toolbar button.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="111" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>These tips can help you identify the function of each button.</source>
